============================================================================
                   ACPI DSDT Table for ad5593r driver

                          Installation Guide
============================================================================

Pre-requirement: Have administrator permission
$ sudo su


Build ACPI table
============================================================================
1. Install acpi tools
   $ sudo apt-get install acpica-tools

2. Modify content of "DSDT.dsl"

3. Generate DSDT.aml (binary)
   $ iasl -tc DSDT.dsl
   if there is something errer, fix it and build again

4. Copy DSDT.aml to the path kernel/firmware/acpi/
   $ cp DSDT.aml kernel/firmware/acpi/DSDT.aml

5. Generate cpio file
   $ find kernel | cpio -H newc --create > adv_gpio_dsdt.cpio


Install step:
============================================================================

1. Copy ACPI table to /boot
   $ cp adv_gpio_dsdt.cpio /boot

2. Edit default grub setting
   $ vim /etc/grub.d/10_linux

3. Modify initrd

  if test -n "${initrd}" && [ x"$GRUB_DISABLE_INITRD" != xtrue ]; then
    # TRANSLATORS: ramdisk isn't identifier. Should be translated.
#    if [ x"$quiet_boot" = x0 ] || [ x"$type" != xsimple ]; then
    if [ x"$quiet_boot" = x0 ]; then
      message="$(gettext_printf "Loading initial ramdisk ...")"
      sed "s/^/$submenu_indentation/" << EOF
        echo    '$(echo "$message" | grub_quote)'
EOF
    fi
    sed "s/^/$submenu_indentation/" << EOF
        initrd  ${rel_dirname}/${initrd}    
        ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
        // modify this line to -->
        initrd  /boot/adv_gpio_dsdt.cpio ${rel_dirname}/${initrd}
EOF


4. Update grub
   $ grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg 

5. Reboot
